2. WORKFLOW-SPECIFIC UX
   For each Kaizen phase (Section 5):
   
   PHASE 1: SCOPING
   Mobile/Web Flow:
   ├─ Step 1: "Describe your process" (form)
   ├─ Step 2: "Who's involved?" (stakeholder form)
   ├─ Step 3: "What's the pain point?" (open-ended + AI suggestions)
   ├─ Step 4: "Review preliminary charter" (generated from inputs)
   ├─ Step 5: "Get approvals" (route to sponsor)
   └─ Result: Signed charter, team ready
   
   UI Pattern:
// Mobile-first, wizard-style <ProgressBar steps={5} currentStep={1} /> <FormSection> <Question>What's the name of this process?</Question> <TextInput placeholder="e.g., Purchase-to-Pay" /> <AssistanceChip>AI: Similar processes: Invoicing, Expense Approval</AssistanceChip> </FormSection> <Actions> <Button secondary>Skip this step</Button> <Button primary>Continue</Button> </Actions>

PHASE 2: BASELINING
Mobile/Web Flow:
├─ Process Map Viewer (shows current-state map derived from events)
├─ Metrics Dashboard (cycle time, errors, cost with confidence intervals)
├─ Data Quality Indicator (coverage %, confidence level, anomalies flagged)
├─ Capture Progress (# sessions captured, # hours covered, # more needed)
├─ Validate Baseline (SME review: "Does this match reality?")
└─ Approve for Improvement (gate: accept baseline before proceeding)

PHASE 3-5: CHARTERING, SCHEDULING, EVENT
├─ Charter Review & Approval
├─ Event Workspace (collaborative area)
├─ Workshop Facilitation Tools
├─ Decision Log (capture decisions during event)
├─ Real-time Voting / Consensus Building
└─ Action Plan Generator

PHASE 6-7: IMPLEMENTATION
├─ Action Tracker Gantt (timeline of all actions)
├─ Task Dashboard (tasks assigned to me, status, blockers)
├─ Escalation Alerts (what's at risk?)
├─ Weekly Status Collection (% complete per action)
└─ Risk Register (what could go wrong? who's tracking?)

PHASE 8: VALIDATION
├─ Before/After Comparison (metrics side-by-side)
├─ Statistical Analysis (confidence intervals, significance testing)
├─ Benefit Report (operational + financial)
├─ Anomaly Detection (results too good? unexpected regression?)
└─ Benefit Approval (gate: approve before publishing)

